trend_summary: 1990s–2020s imagery shows largely forest- and field-dominated countryside. Small pockets of housing and farm structures expanded slowly along main roads, with minor infill and a few new cul-de-sacs. Some cropland reverted to woodland, and scattered clear-cuts appear. Road network remains stable; no major industrial or commercial hubs emerge. Overall character stays rural and sparsely built.
notable_changes: Gradual ribbon housing growth along the north–south arterial road.
Emergence of two small residential cul-de-sac clusters near the central settlement core.
Several former crop fields in the east show forest regrowth.
New clear-cut forestry patches visible in southwestern highlands by final image.
No significant expansion of commercial or industrial footprints throughout period.
